    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a pot with a matching lid over a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-kedgeree-with-boiled-egg-and-peas/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>smoked basa fillet[s]</strong> into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[525ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-kedgeree-with-boiled-egg-and-peas/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil a full kettle</p><p>Once softened, add your <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>to the pot with your <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric </strong>and <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-kedgeree-with-boiled-egg-and-peas/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chopped basa </strong>and <strong>vegetable stock </strong>to the pot and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-14 min or until all the water has absorbed and the basa is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-kedgeree-with-boiled-egg-and-peas/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, add your <strong>egg[s]</strong> to a separate pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for exactly 8 min for perfect, mid-boiled egg[s], then fill a bowl of <strong>very cold water</strong> and add the <strong>cooked egg[s] </strong>to the bowl</p><p>Set aside</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-kedgeree-with-boiled-egg-and-peas/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once the rice is cooked, add your <strong>blanched peas </strong>and <strong>spinach</strong> to the pot and give everything a good mix up until the spinach starts to wilt \u2013 this is your <strong>smoked basa kedgeree</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-kedgeree-with-boiled-egg-and-peas/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel the <strong>cooled egg[s]</strong> and cut them in half</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-kedgeree-with-boiled-egg-and-peas/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>smoked basa kedgeree </strong>and top with the<strong> halved boiled egg[s]</strong></p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
